VISION IMAGE ANALYZE SMART ASPECT RATIOS

The `--smartaspectratios` argument is used to specify the aspect ratios to use for smart cropping. Smart cropping is used to find a representative sub-region of the image for thumbnail generation, with priority given to include faces.

USAGE: ai vision image analyze --smartaspectratios <ratios,> [...other options]

EXAMPLE

  ai vision image analyze --file image.jpg --visualfeatures SmartCrops --smartaspectratios 1:1,16:9